UML:TaggedValue.value: uStore will manage groups. Every group will include any kind of users. - Group will not do any uploads/downloads directly, only users inside the group will log-in to uStore - In every group will exist at least one group admin user that have the permissions to add/delete other group mates and define their permissions - Group profile will include general information about the group

uStore will allow the user to subscribe to AAL services or categories and be notified when new AAL Services or updates are available - uStore will propose users an update for installed software. Update can require a fee; in such case the update will always be optional. - uStore will allow users to subscribe for news on available AAL services or updates (like RSS feed)

System will save user profile that will include: - Identity management, e.g. using open ID - Username and password - Is Administrator - Optional: Type of user: End-User, Relative etc with possible connection to other user - Permissions like permission to upload new services - Zero or more groups that the user belongs to and is he group admin user there - General information about the user (how will be contacted, who is he, geographic location, specific data per role: what are user's needs, what are his handicaps (e.g. blind), what are provider's abilities, what business models are supported by provider etc.) - History of previous service orders, service offers and contracts the user signed - Link to existing AAL platform profiles uploaded to uStore - Optional: filled manually platform profile details: hardware platform, software that is already installed etc. - Saved items that the user is interested to order later - Services and groups that the user asked to receive update notification about them - If the user has a profile on develop depot/s with different username/password, it can be saved in profile

uStore will support two main roles: administrators (part with legal responsibilities, different administrators can have different permissions) and users (who can play different role for different services, like service providers, developers, authorities) The view of the site that will be shown to user or administrator will be different. The permissions to do different tasks on uStore site will be based on specific user id.

System will interact with AAL platform profile (separate for home, mobile etc) AAL platform profile includes: - Hardware devices - Installed software (uAAL & external) - Configuration and personalization As default, AAL platform profile is saved on the user's platform. It will be uploaded (for backup and better search) to uStore after receiving permission from the user. If the user is not interested to upload the platform profile to server, it will propose to user to use the data in platform profile by uStore search engine for improving search but without saving for future use (only for specific session/search). - Will be defined interface between uStore and AAL platform (maybe by uStore client) for this interaction. - Will be developed automatic update mechanism without interaction from the user side (after once defining necessary permissions) - System will ask for association with user profile/s. The rule about platform profile will be: reuse the data as much as possible and don't bother user with same questions.
System will require that during the registration every user of the uStore will fill questionnaire for filling his user profile.
